The structural performance of the SSSG bridges is assessed in terms of the interaction equa-
tion, which has long been recognized as design limit state and allows for the quantification of
the demand-to-capacity ratio [
]. It is critical to emphasize that this interaction equation,
defining the ultimate limit state, is used for structural elements subjected to simultaneous
action of bending moments and axial loads.
